  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nWhen doing audits, the audits are performed at a specific version of the github repo. When running:\r\n\r\n```\r\nforge install\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere isn't a way to currently get the specific hash we want. \r\n\r\nPerhaps something like\r\n\r\n```\r\nforge install <https:// git URL> --hash <commit-hash>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd behind the scenes it does:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngit clone <org/repo>\r\ncd lib/repo\r\ngit checkout <commit-hash>\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
