    "body": "This is already possible with `forge install https://github.com/<user>/<repo>@<tag>`\r\n\r\nSee:\r\n```sh\r\n$ forge install --help\r\nInstall one or multiple dependencies. If no arguments are provided, then existing dependencies will\r\nbe installed.\r\n\r\nUsage: forge install [OPTIONS] [DEPENDENCIES]...\r\n    forge install [OPTIONS] <github username>/<github project>@<tag>...\r\n    forge install [OPTIONS] <alias>=<github username>/<github project>@<tag>...\r\n    forge install [OPTIONS] <https:// git url>...\r\n    \r\n ...\r\n \r\n Additionally, a ref can be provided by adding @ to the dependency path.\r\n\r\n          A ref can be: - A branch: master - A tag: v1.2.3 - A commit: 8e8128\r\n```",
